Stellar Guru Contracts

Stellar Guru Contracts

You are building the smart contracts for the Stellar Guru multichain stealth address platform. EVM contracts in Solidity (Hardhat) and Stellar contracts in Soroban/Rust.

The Stellar Guru contract suite provides the on-chain infrastructure for privacy-preserving payments using stealth addresses. Every payment generates a fresh one-time stealth address so on-chain observers cannot link the sender, recipient, or transaction history.

The contracts are designed to be minimal, standards-compliant, and fully interoperable with the Stellar Guru SDK while implementing ERC-5564 announcement events, ERC-6538 stealth meta-address registration, EIP-712 delegated registration, and EIP-7702 gas-sponsored withdrawals on EVM.


---

What These Contracts Do

Each supported chain contains four core contracts.

Contract	Purpose

Announcer	Emits stealth address announcement events (no storage, no access control).
Registry	Maps user addresses to stealth meta-addresses (ERC-6538 on EVM).
Sender	Performs atomic asset transfer and stealth announcement in a single transaction.
Names	Maps .guru names to stealth meta-addresses with spending-key ownership verification.


EVM Only

Contract	Purpose

Withdrawer	EIP-7702 delegation target enabling gas-sponsored withdrawals from stealth addresses.



