— Continuous Integration (CI)

Create:

.github/workflows/ci.yml

The workflow validates both EVM and Stellar implementations on every push and pull request.

name: CI

on:
  push:
    branches: [main]

  pull_request:
    branches: [main]

jobs:

  evm:
    runs-on: ubuntu-latest

    defaults:
      run:
        working-directory: evm

    steps:
      - uses: actions/checkout@v4

      - uses: actions/setup-node@v4
        with:
          node-version: 22

      - run: npm ci

      - run: npx prettier --check .

      - run: npx hardhat compile

      - run: npx hardhat test

  stellar:
    runs-on: ubuntu-latest

    defaults:
      run:
        working-directory: stellar

    steps:
      - uses: actions/checkout@v4

      - uses: stellar/setup-soroban@v1

      - run: cargo fmt --check --manifest-path Cargo.toml

      - run: cargo test --workspace

The CI pipeline must ensure:

Successful EVM dependency installation

Successful Solidity compilation

Successful Hardhat test execution

Successful Soroban formatting checks

Successful Soroban workspace tests


A pull request should not be merged until every CI job completes successfully.
